		<!-- message -->
		<div>Monk 15/Thief 5/White Mage 4.<br />
<br />
Once I get to 18 with monk (chose it for soloing ability), doing subjob quest and becoming a white mage/monk subclass. If I get to 30 with that, making white mage a subclass and going bard or beastmaster as main job. I've been a cleric, being a pure healer is a mixed blessing - always get groups, but your time is never your own - and that seems very much more the case in FFXI, where healing power is concentrated primarily in white mage, with red mages, summoners, bards and paladins adding not a lot to that. Probably the one saving grace is that when you are dead, you can't search for a white mage to rez you.<br />
<br />
DAoC had similar issues - in both, you can't rez yourself, so you as a rezzer almost ALWAYS take the experience loss that you save everyone else. FFXI has the most crippling experience loss of any game. In the high end EQ game, you almost never lose significant experience no matter what you do. You have three hours to find a rez, and you can log out for up to a week and get one six days later if you like. In DAoC, you lost a good amount of experience if you had to release, but you could return to where you died and get some portion of that back. Also, DAoC is a far smaller world that that of FFXI, and if you weren't in the middle of utter nowhere between realms, probably one of the two or three classes in your realm that could rez, would come by. All rez-capable classes get a decent rez for free at level 10 in DAoC.<br />
<br />
FFXI has a one hour limit to find a rez, during which time you can't do a /sea to find a white mage. And even if you did find one, it could take an enormous amount of time for a white mage to get to you. Here's the kicker about experience loss. Experience given is based on your relative level to the monster. An even con monster gives 100 xp. At my highest level, 15, an even con monster will kill me easily. A decent challenge monster (gives 36-72 points) that has high defense or evasion will kill me. A decent challenge monster that has low evasion or defense MAY kill me, depending on what techniques I have up, whether I am full health, and how often my weapon procs. So most of the time I kill easy prey, which give 12-25 points per kill.<br />
<br />
So. Level 1 takes 500 points to get through. You normally fight even or decent challenge mobs, so if you die (losing 50 xp), one kill will make up the loss.<br />
<br />
Level 14 took me 3400 points to get through. That is about 135 kills total, and about 13 kills to make up the loss when dead. That's about an hour (and ten hours to get through the level solo). By the time I hit 25, and white mages get their first raise spell (returning 25% experience), each death could easily take a night of hard exp grind with no further deaths to recover from!<br />
<br />
Anyway. That diverged a bit from the topic. One final note: In a group in Fort Ghelslpa, fighting even-&gt;tough monsters, in a full group, I made about the same experience as I would fighting easy-challenge monsters at the tough end of a newbie field.<br />
<br />
I group with a red mage a lot, and I wish he would bind (root) the mob, poison and bio it, and then just med and keep me cured instead of running around meleeing it and causing downtime. I don't care if you have a sword; you have magic, I don't, all medding does for me is drain my TP.<br />
<br />
What was the question?</div>
